Key Match Events: Jose Altuve and Jeremy Peña homered as the Houston Astros improved to 7-0 in games started by Yusei Kikuchi by beating the scuffling Arizona Diamondbacks 11-5 on Saturday.
Jose Altuve homered to left (368 feet) in the 7th inning.
Jeremy Peña homered to right center (390 feet), scoring Diaz and Bregman in the 6th inning.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Astros improved to 7-0 in games started by Yusei Kikuchi.
The game was played at Daikin Park in Houston, Texas, with an attendance of 35,739.
